          {
            "commit": "a66e12d6ede2afda3bb7a5b1f22b8c17c1176584",
            "subject": "LU-216 ldiskfs: use proper arguments for ldiskfs_free_blocks"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Nathaniel Clark",
          "email": "nathaniel.l.clark@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-21 18:08:30.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-28 15:35:05.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5091 build: Support alternate locations of libzfs.so",
        "message": "LU-5091 build: Support alternate locations of libzfs.so\n\nDue to the change for with-zfs-devel (LU-3497), also add support to\nsearch for libzfs.so along with the alternate locations supplied with\nthe header files.\nAlso need to unpack zfs{,-devel}.  The zfs RPM is needed because it\nhas the actual libraries in it and the zfs-devel RPM only has un-\nversioned symlinks to the libraries in the zfs RPM.\nThis will all change one day when we have a libzfs RPM per\nhttps://github.com/zfsonlinux/zfs/issues/2329 and it looks like it\ncould be one day soon: https://github.com/zfsonlinux/zfs/pull/2341.\n\nSigned-off-by: Nathaniel Clark <nathaniel.l.clark@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Brian J. Murrell <brian.murrell@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ic78bd0eb88d8ab0f2456b8cf684bb8b9c0c0833a\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/10401\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
